EE 21 
Fundamentals of Electronics (4)  
Semiconductor theory; operation, characteristics, models and basic circuits of electronic devices; large-and small-signal modeling and analysis; biasing circuits; transistor amplifiers and switches; frequency response; feedback; operational amplifiers  
6 hrs (3 class, 3 lab)  
PR. EE 12 and EE 18  
(1,2) 
